      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "thorns",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The Greek word means, probably, a kind of acacia, or perhaps “thistles.” There is a Greek proverb ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "οὐ γὰρ ἄκανθαι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “no thistles,” i. e. “nothing useless.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
